Idea 0 introduces a robust binary search framework that adapts to up to $ k $ erroneous responses using consistency scoring, Bayesian filtering, and regret-based adaptation. While it integrates ideas from robust search (e.g., Rényi-Ulam games) and strategic reasoning (inspired by auto-bidding models), its core mechanism—adaptive bisection with fault detection and local re-evaluation—has precedents in the literature on noisy binary search and adversarial bandits. The use of hindsight rationality is interesting but applied in a relatively instrumental way. Thus, while strong, it represents an elegant *synthesis* rather than a fundamental *departure*.

